{
  "stem": "27507.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm not quite sure where to.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the one place that I remember, the one memory that I have is that we went to-- we came to a place called Miedzyrecz, which was a-- a little town, a shtetl.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that must have been Yom Kippur or-- or the evening of Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I went with my father to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that synagogue was, of course, a very, very traditional synagogue.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember still those figures of praying people covered in their tallis and the yellow candles.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It-- it was really something which I never saw before, so it was, of course, a very vivid memory.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then we came back to Rowne, I think, for a short time and still stayed for some days in Rowne.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were after that wandering.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "All together, the eastern Poland was-- it was a real wandering of the nations.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "People were moving from one place to another, because nobody knew where it is better, where it is safer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There were absolutely incredible masses of refugees who had lost their houses and lost their possessions and they were going from one place to another.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we lost track, as well, of-- of-- of the family that we came to Rowne, my-- the sister of my father and with her family.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She moved later to Wilno.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we finally, after another some weeks, we came to Bialystok, which is another town in northeastern Poland.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the family or part of the family of my mother was there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "How they got there and what they were exactly doing there, I'm not sure.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But there was my mother and my-- and my parents and a couple of aunts, couple of her sisters, and my grandmother, my mother's mother, and some other family members.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
